item.title: How Does Golf's Four-Ball Better-Ball Format Work?
item.description: Four-ball is a team format in golf where a team of two golfers each play their own golf ball. The teammate with the lower score on each hole provides that team’s score for that hole.  For this reason, the format is also often called Four-ball Better Ball (4BBB) as the better score of the pair is counted each time. The format can be used in stroke play or match play, such as in the Ryder Cup or Solheim Cup.

item.title: Why do baby teeth turn pink?
item.description: A quick side note: loose baby teeth might turn pink. This happens a lot. A pink tooth is likely pretty hollow, and may fracture into two or more pieces. Why do baby teeth go pink? Internal resorption makes space inside the crown which allows blood vessels to fill out the chamber.
